 Here's a simple JavaScript program that generates and prints out the ASCII characters and their corresponding hexadecimal codes for values from 0 to 7F:

```javascript
for (var i = 0; i <= 127; i++) {
    var asciiChar = String.fromCharCode(i);
    var hexCode = i.toString(16).toUpperCase();

    console.log("ASCII Character: " + asciiChar + ", Hex Code: 0x" + hexCode);
}
```

This program uses a `for` loop to iterate through the values from 0 to 127 (which is equivalent to 7F in hexadecimal). For each value, it converts it into an ASCII character using the `String.fromCharCode()` method and then converts it into its corresponding hexadecimal code using the `toString(16)` method. Finally, it prints out both the ASCII character and its hexadecimal code to the console.
